.TH "nau8540_set_tdm_slot" 9 "nau8540_set_tdm_slot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nau8540_set_tdm_slot \- configure DAI TX TDM.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nau8540_set_tdm_slot
.BI "(struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ","
.BI "unsigned int tx_mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rx_mask "  ","
.BI "int slots "  ","
.BI "int slot_width "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dai" 12
DAI
.IP "tx_mask" 12
bitmask representing active TX slots. Ex.
0xf for normal 4 channel TDM.
0xf0 for shifted 4 channel TDM
.IP "rx_mask" 12
no used.
.IP "slots" 12
Number of slots in use.
.IP "slot_width" 12
Width in bits for each slot.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Configures a DAI for TDM operation. Only support 4 slots TDM.
